shee
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A poor implementation of `tree` in plain `sh`.

Screenshot: https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36552788/125976452-f2aa0db1-c79d-459f-8eea-dc6ecc066e70.png


install
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Clone the repo

    $ git clone https://github.com/fehawen/shee.git

Change working directory to shee

    $ cd shee

Install shee

    $ make install

Add ~/.bin to PATH in $SHELL's startup file

    export PATH=~/bin:$PATH


usage
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

shee [OPTION]... [DIRECTORY]...

With no DIRECTORY, default to using \`\$PWD\`.

Exclude directories by assigning a colon separated list
to SHEE_IGNORE_DIRS in \$SHELL\'s startup file.

Example: export SHEE_IGNORE_DIRS=.git:cache:build

  -d, --dirs-only          only show directories in output
  -h, --help               display this help and exit
